    "name": "Grid Independence Study — Centrifugal Pump CFD Mesh Refinement",
    "description": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted across three grid levels (coarse 1.2M cells, medium 4.8M cells, fine 18.6M cells) to verify discretization-independent prediction of hemolysis index. Richardson extrapolation applied to quantify grid convergence index (GCI) for wall shear stress and velocity magnitude at five operating points. Target GCI < 5% on the fine grid. Study performed using ANSYS Fluent 2023R1 with k-omega SST turbulence closure.",
    "activityType": "GridConvergenceStudy",
